Kuwait several years before the Gulf War.<EOS> She noted then that women customarily
walked about 10 feet behind their husbands.<EOS> She returned to Kuwait recently and
observed that the men now walked several yards behind their wives.<EOS> Ms. Walters
approached one of the women and said, "This is marvelous.<EOS> Can you tell the free
world just what enabled women here to achieve this reversal of roles?"<EOS> 

"Land mines," said the Kuwaiti woman.<EOS> 

