Where is the "simple" explanation of the transportation piece?<EOS> 

As I have told RNR, I think we should advise Duke in writing that its IP is not
in conformity with the contract, sinceit is in the alternative, and that our IP
is hence the only one that will be before the arbitrators (since Duke clearly
cannot change it's ineffective IP at this stage, having already seen ours).<EOS>
