---------------------------------------------------------------------<EOS> <<Doctor
RODERIGO LOPEZ (1525 -1594) was the Portugese Jewish doctor accused by Essex of
trying to poison Queen Elizabeth.<EOS> The 69 year old Dr. Lopez was found guilty and
was summarily hung and quartered on June 7, 1594 at Tyburn.<EOS> Long before
(September 1560) Dr. Lopez had been the personal house doctor of Robert Dudley
and the good doctor was obligated to write the death certificate for Amy Robsart
(stating that she had "accidentally" fallen down the stairs).<EOS> That same year
(1560) a Spanish priest named RUY LOPEZ handily beat all comers at a chess
tournament in Rome.<EOS> Lopez's 1561 book "Libro de la invencion liberal y arte del
Juego del Acedraz" became THE classic on Chess openings, including the one that
bears his name.<EOS>
